==== Installing YARA ====
BEFORE INSTALLING:
  YARA comes pre-packaged with the Cuckoo installation. If you are still having trouble, use the steps below to 
  install the latest version of YARA into the Cuckoo Host. The commands below are for Linux, specifically Debian. 

Notes:
  - View Latest Version Here: https://github.com/virustotal/yara/releases/latest
  - View Documentation Here for 3.10.0: https://yara.readthedocs.io/en/v3.10.0/
  - View GitHub Project Here: https://github.com/virustotal/yara
  - View Main Website here: http://virustotal.github.io/yara/
  - Make sure you have automake, libtool, make, and gcc in your Debian or Ubuntu System:
        $ sudo apt-get install automake libtool make gcc

-- Steps to install YARA --
  Install dependecies:

        $ sudo apt-get install libtool autoconf automake libssl-dev libjansson-dev libmagic-dev
    
  Install checkinstall to build a package (note, I have not tried this when installing Cuckoo):

        $ sudo apt-get install checkinstall

  Install YARA:

        $ wget https://github.com/VirusTotal/yara/archive/v3.10.0.tar.gz -O yara-3.10.0.tar.gz
    
  Extract the tarball
  
        $ tar -zxf yara-3.10.0.tar.gz
    
  Build, Complile and Install YARA with OpenSSL-dependent feautres enforced, the Cuckoo Module and the Magic Module
  
        $ cd yara-3.10.0
        $ ./bootstrap.sh
        $ ./configure --with-crypto --enable-cuckoo --enable-magic
        $ make
        $ sudo make install
        
  Validate the installation
        $ yara -v
        The Result of the command should look similar to this depending on what version you install:
            yara 3.10.0
  Run the test cases to make sure that everything is fine:

        $ make check

  Once the new YARA package has been installed, install the YARA Python bindings:

        $ cd yara-python
        $ python setup.py build
        $ sudo python setup.py install

  Validate the installation:

        $ pip show yara-python
    
        The Result of the command should look similar to this:
            Name: yara-python
            Version: 3.4.0
            Location: /usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages
            Requires:
    
  YARA is now sucssesfully installed.    
    

-- YARA Install Commands without notes (excluding commands I did NOT use):

    $ sudo apt-get install libtool autoconf automake libssl-dev libjansson-dev libmagic-dev
    $ wget https://github.com/VirusTotal/yara/archive/v3.10.0.tar.gz -O yara-3.10.0.tar.gz
    $ tar -zxf yara-3.10.0.tar.gz
    $ cd yara-3.10.0
    $ ./bootstrap.sh
    $ ./configure --with-crypto --enable-cuckoo --enable-magic
    $ make
    $ sudo make install
    $ yara -v
    $ make check
    $ cd yara-python
    $ python setup.py build
    $ sudo python setup.py install
    $ pip show yara-python
          The Result of the command should look similar to this:
              Name: yara-python
              Version: 3.4.0
              Location: /usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages
              Requires:
    
  YARA is now sucssesfully installed.   
  
  
